definition: to come up/to approach/(verb complement indicating success)
on top/upon/above/upper/previous/first (of multiple parts)/to climb/to get onto/to go up/to attend (class or university)
see 上聲|上声[shang3 sheng1]
to come/to arrive/to come round/ever since/next

sentences.english: In fact, I usually don't catch anything.
sentences.chinese: 事实上，我通常什么都钓不上来。

sentences.english: They only had time for three people to climb up. Julia climbed up the rope.
sentences.chinese: 更恐怖但是时间紧迫，只容得下三个人爬上来。

sentences.english: He pulled a would-be suicide out of a river.
sentences.chinese: 他将一位自杀未遂者从河里拖上来。

sentences.english: Let your focus be on guiding your children to develop actual discipline.
sentences.chinese: 让你的重点落在指导孩子形成真正的纪律自制上来。

sentences.english: Joshua therefore commanded the priests, saying, Come ye up out of Jordan.
sentences.chinese: 你吩咐抬法柜的祭司从约旦河里上来。

sentences.english: How the hell did he get to be a pezzonovante, Hagen wondered.
sentences.chinese: 黑根在想，他怎么就做到总统顾问上来了。

sentences.english: 'Jump up, ' said the man. 'Is that your boy?
sentences.chinese: “上来吧，”车把式说道，“这是你儿子？”

sentences.english: Write it in your workbooks and give it in tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 写在你的作业本上明天交上来。

sentences.english: With one last heave, the net was hauled in.
sentences.chinese: 随着最后的一下猛拉，网被拖了上来。

sentences.english: Water inched its way up the steps as first as first-floor outside walls collapsed.
sentences.chinese: 当一楼外墙塌陷时水慢慢地沿着台阶漫了上来。

sentences.english: Someone brought cold cuts, dark bread, and beer from the jeep.
sentences.chinese: 有人把吉普车上的冻肉，黑面包和啤酒送上来。

sentences.english: Oh, one more thing, I've ordered another dish, stuffed pork chop. Can it be served sooner?
sentences.chinese: 对了，我还点了一个酿猪扒，能否快些上来？

sentences.english: The sun rose and smiled on it.
sentences.chinese: 太阳升上来了，向无名花微笑。

sentences.english: Get ahead and know that some of those things they'll catch back up.
sentences.chinese: 往前走，明白有些事情他们会重新追上来。

sentences.english: Your car has heave-hoed out of the lake.
sentences.chinese: 你的汽车已从湖中拉上来了。

to return/to come back
to come over/to manage/to handle/to be able to take care of

this side/here
to come and see/to see a topic from a certain point of view
to go in
to see/to look at/to read/to watch/to visit/to call on/to consider/to regard as/to look after/to treat (an illness)/to depend on/to feel (that)/(after verb) to give it a try/Watch out! (for a danger)
to look after/to take care of/to watch/to guard
as to/considering/for
ahead/in front/preceding/above/also pr. [qian2 mian5]
to go down/to descend/to go on/to continue/(of a servant) to withdraw
to catch and hold on/to continue/to go on to do sth/to follow/to carry on/then/after that/subsequently/to proceed/to ensue/in turn/in one's turn
to stand up/to get up/also pr. [qi3 lai2]

(after a verb) indicating the beginning and continuation of an action or a state/indicating an upward movement (e.g. after 站[zhan4])/indicating completion/(after a perception verb, e.g. 看[kan4]) expressing preliminary judgment/also pr. [qi3 lai5]
